From the manufacturer

ASUS Vivobook Go 15

Be productive as you Go

It’s light. It’s compact. It’s the ASUS Vivobook Go 15, and it’s designed to make you productive and keep you entertained wherever you go! With its 180° lay-flat hinge, physical webcam shield and loads of thoughtful design features. Vivobook Go 15 is the laptop that sets you free!

Features at a glance...

  • Windows 11 Home
  • AMD Ryzen 3 7520U Mobile Processor
  • 8GB RAM, paired with 256GB M.2 NVMe PCIE 3.0 SSD
  • UK layout Keyboard
  • This Vivobook 15 comes with Cortana and Alexa voice-recognition support

Outstanding audio to hear the world

Vivobook Go 15 provides incredibly powerful, crystal-clear sound with ASUS SonicMaster and DTS Audio Processing. The combination of hardware and software boost the volume, and remove noise to improve audio clarity so you get truly immersive sound.

Choose your color

Vivobook Go 15 is available in three colors: the never-out-of-fashion Mixed Black and Cool Silver, and the brand-new cozy Grey Green. While matching your style, Vivobook Go 54 is also slim enough to slip into your bag, and light enough for easy one-handed carrying.

Wide open for sharing

Vivobook Go 15 features a precision-engineered, 180° lay-flat hinge that makes it easy to share content or collaborate with others.

Perfect in every detail

Vivobook Go 15 keeps you fully connected with its comprehensive I/O ports. There are a USB-C 3.2 Gen 1 port, a USB 3.2 Gen 1 Type-A ports, a USB 2.0 port, HDMI output and an audio combo jack — so it’s easy to connect all your existing peripherals, displays and projectors.

Fine-tuned with ASUS WiFi Master technology

Vivobook Go 15 offers a comprehensive range of wireless connectivity. WiFi 6E5 (802.11ax) allows you to load online content in the blink of an eye.

World’s most strictly tested US military-grade laptop durability

ASUS laptops are engineered with extraordinary toughness meet the exacting US MIL-STD-810H military-grade standard, undergoing 12 test methods and 26 test procedures exceeding industry standards.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    4.0 out of 5 stars Fast, powerful, light, let down by mediocre screen.
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 23 August 2023
    Verified Purchase
    I bought this laptop for my school age great-niece, in the past she was given 10-year-old laptops upgraded with SSDs which were a help, but with 2nd gen Intel i5 and only 720p screen resolution, still left a lot to be desired. I spent a day setting the laptop up for her, I was immediately disappointed by the screen which lacks colour depth, reds appearing closer to orange and blues also weak. Furthermore, I called Amazon to arrange for a return, which they agreed to. However, a few days later when the family came round to see the laptop, it was agreed that they were happy to keep it. When I looked at alternatives such as the Acer Aspire 5 looking at the screen specs, these were hardly better. I have perhaps been spoilt by my various ASUS and Samsung OLED screens and higher end Razer Advanced, and a 6-year-old Dell XPS. Unfortunately, the OLED version of this laptop costs several hundred £ more. In other respects, it excels in speed and remains relatively cool thanks to the Ryzen processor.
